News Coo
========

This project is built on top of the following open-source work. All of it
is MIT-licensed and used in accordance with each project's terms.

Defuddle
--------
News Coo depends on Defuddle (https://github.com/kepano/defuddle) by
@kepano for main-content extraction and HTML→Markdown conversion. Defuddle
is consumed as an npm dependency; no source is vendored.

  Copyright (c) Steph Ango (kepano)
  License: MIT

Obsidian Web Clipper
--------------------
News Coo's content-script extraction wrapper (in src/content/) adapts the
pattern used by Obsidian Web Clipper
(https://github.com/obsidianmd/obsidian-clipper) for invoking Defuddle,
shadow-DOM flattening, and relative-URL normalization. Approximately 100
lines of TypeScript follow that approach. No template engine, highlighter,
reader-mode, side-panel, or interpreter code is reused.

  Copyright (c) Obsidian
  License: MIT

Toast Translate
---------------
The build-system layout (rolldown + vitest + happy-dom + ESLint
TypeScript-strict configuration) is patterned after Toast Translate
(https://github.com/lawrencelinky/toast-translate) by Lawrence Lin.
Configuration files are similar by convention; no runtime source is
reused.

  Copyright (c) 2026 Lawrence Lin
